issues.title: Infotainment System Freezing and Unresponsiveness
issues.description: The central infotainment display frequently freezes, becomes unresponsive, or displays error messages. System may require hard reset or complete replacement.
issues.fix_description: Software update, module reset, or complete infotainment system replacement
issues.prevention: Keep software updated, avoid extreme temperatures, gentle operation of touch screen

issues.title: Carbon Fiber Roof Panel Delamination
issues.description: Carbon fiber roof panels show signs of delamination, bubbling, or separation from the underlying structure, particularly around edges and mounting points.
issues.fix_description: Complete roof panel replacement or professional re-bonding of carbon fiber layers
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperature changes, regular inspection, proper storage

issues.title: Dual-Clutch Transmission Jerky Operation
issues.description: The 8-speed dual-clutch transmission exhibits jerky shifts, hesitation during acceleration, or rough engagement from standstill, particularly in stop-and-go traffic.
issues.fix_description: Software calibration update, clutch adjustment, or transmission overhaul
issues.prevention: Smooth driving habits, regular transmission service, avoid aggressive starts

issues.title: Electronic Parking Brake Malfunction
issues.description: Electronic parking brake system fails to engage or disengage properly, sometimes leaving the vehicle immobilized or creating safety concerns.
issues.fix_description: Electronic module replacement, actuator repair, or software recalibration
issues.prevention: Regular brake system maintenance, avoid forcing the system

issues.title: Front Suspension Component Premature Wear
issues.description: Front suspension components including control arms, bushings, and ball joints show premature wear, leading to handling issues and noise.
issues.fix_description: Replace worn suspension components, alignment correction
issues.prevention: Avoid potholes, regular alignment checks, smooth driving

issues.title: Battery Drain and Electrical Issues
issues.description: Excessive battery drain when parked, leading to dead battery situations. May be caused by various electronic modules not entering sleep mode properly.
issues.fix_description: Software updates, module replacement, parasitic draw diagnosis and repair
issues.prevention: Regular driving, battery maintenance, software updates

issues.title: Paint Defects and Clear Coat Issues
issues.description: Paint quality issues including orange peel texture, clear coat defects, and premature fading or discoloration, particularly on certain color options.
issues.fix_description: Professional paint correction, panel repainting, or clear coat refinishing
issues.prevention: Proper washing techniques, covered parking, paint protection film

issues.title: Air Conditioning Compressor Failure
issues.description: A/C compressor fails prematurely, leading to loss of cooling function and potential damage to other A/C system components.
issues.fix_description: Compressor replacement, system flush, and refrigerant recharge
issues.prevention: Regular A/C system maintenance, annual service checks

issues.title: Door Handle Mechanism Failure
issues.description: Retractable door handles fail to extend or retract properly, potentially trapping occupants or preventing entry to the vehicle.
issues.fix_description: Door handle mechanism replacement, motor repair, or software recalibration
issues.prevention: Gentle operation, regular lubrication, avoid forcing handles

issues.title: Fuel System Vapor Lock Issues
issues.description: Fuel system experiences vapor lock conditions in hot weather, causing engine hesitation, stalling, or difficulty starting after heat soak.
issues.fix_description: Fuel system insulation improvement, fuel pump replacement, or ventilation system modification
issues.prevention: Use high-quality fuel, avoid extended idling in hot weather, proper ventilation

editorial.hero_blurb: The Roma resurrects the golden age of Italian grand touring with contemporary performance prowess. This isn't just transportation—it's a love letter to la dolce vita wrapped in 612 horsepower.
editorial.essence: Ferrari's most sophisticated GT blends timeless Italian elegance with cutting-edge performance technology. The Roma proves that modern Ferraris can be both breathtakingly beautiful and devastatingly fast, offering a more refined alternative to the brand's track-focused supercars.
editorial.heritage: Named after Rome, the eternal city, the Roma draws inspiration from Ferrari's legendary front-engined grand tourers of the 1950s and 60s. It continues the bloodline of the 250 GT and Daytona, reimagined for the modern era with contemporary luxury and performance.
editorial.design_philosophy: Clean, unadorned elegance defines the Roma's aesthetic—a deliberate departure from Ferrari's more aggressive designs. Every line serves both beauty and aerodynamics, creating a timeless silhouette that honors Ferrari's golden age while looking decidedly forward.
editorial.motorsport_history: While not directly descended from race cars, the Roma carries Ferrari's competition DNA through its advanced aerodynamics and chassis technology developed from decades of Formula 1 and sports car racing experience.
editorial.engine_character: The twin-turbo V8 delivers explosive power with surprising refinement, building boost smoothly from 3,000 RPM before unleashing a tsunami of torque. It's muscular yet sophisticated—more cultured than the 488's screaming naturally aspirated predecessor.
editorial.transmission_feel: The 8-speed dual-clutch transmission shifts with lightning precision, seamlessly adapting from smooth grand touring comfort to razor-sharp track aggression. Paddle shifts deliver satisfying mechanical engagement when desired.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: Perfectly balanced between comfort and performance, the Roma's chassis adapts beautifully to different driving scenarios. The Side Slip Control system allows controlled oversteer for experienced drivers while maintaining safety for all skill levels.
editorial.steering_feel: Precise and communicative without being harsh, the steering provides excellent feedback about road conditions and grip levels. It's perfectly weighted for both spirited canyon runs and relaxed highway cruising.
editorial.brake_confidence: Carbon-ceramic brakes deliver phenomenal stopping power with excellent modulation and fade resistance. The pedal feel is progressive and confidence-inspiring, perfect for both track days and emergency stops.
editorial.sound_signature: A sophisticated symphony that ranges from a cultured burble at idle to a spine-tingling roar at full throttle. The exhaust note is distinctly Ferrari—emotional and stirring without being obnoxious in residential areas.
editorial.ideal_owner: Successful professionals who appreciate understated elegance over flashy ostentation, wanting Ferrari performance in a package sophisticated enough for business dinners and weekend getaways alike.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Track-day addicts seeking maximum performance, buyers wanting maximum attention-grabbing drama, or those prioritizing practicality over style and performance.
editorial.buyers_summary: The Roma represents Ferrari's most mature and sophisticated offering—a true grand tourer that doesn't compromise performance for elegance. It's the perfect entry point into Ferrari ownership for discerning buyers who value refinement alongside raw capability.
